---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How The Savvy Granny handles your information and protects your privacy."
>
  <article class="container page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: June 2026</em></p>

    <p>
      The Savvy Granny ("we," "us," or "our") operates the website
      <strong>thesavvygranny.com</strong>. This page explains what information we collect
      and how we use it. We keep things simple and we respect your privacy.
    </p>

    <h2>Information we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Information you give us.</strong> When you submit a recipe or contact us
        through a form, we collect the details you provide (such as your name, email
        address, and recipe content) so we can respond and, with your permission, publish
        your recipe.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Basic usage data.</strong> Like most websites, we may collect anonymous
        analytics (such as pages visited and general location) to understand what content
        is helpful. This does not identify you personally.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we use your information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To respond to your messages and publish recipes you've shared (with credit).</li>
      <li>To improve our recipes and the website.</li>
      <li>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal information to anyone.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Our site may use cookies or similar technologies for basic analytics and to make the
      site work properly. You can disable cookies in your browser settings at any time.
    </p>

    <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
    <p>
      Some links on this site are affiliate links, meaning we may earn a commission if you
      make a purchase — at no extra cost to you. See our
      <a href="/disclosure">affiliate disclosure</a> for details.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      We use trusted third-party services to run this site (for example, form handling,
      hosting, and social sharing such as Pinterest). These services have their own privacy
      policies governing how they handle data.
    </p>

    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <p>
      You can ask us to update or delete any personal information you've shared by
      <a href="/contact">contacting us</a>. We'll be happy to help.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy? Please <a href="/contact">get in touch</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="muted"><em>This is a standard starter privacy policy and not legal advice. As the
    site grows you may want to have it reviewed for your specific situation.</em></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page { max-width: 720px; padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem 2rem; }
  .page h1 { font-size: 2.3rem; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .page h2 { font-size: 1.35rem; margin-top: 1.8rem; }
  .page p, .page li { font-size: 1.04rem; }
</style>
